notesStmt.note: Some infills at corners and edges.
Usage stains, dirty fingerprints, smeared ink.
Ink mostly brown, haloing with some burn-through.
Leather binding slightly rubbed at corners and edges, damaged endcaps .
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 28; written lines: 28; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Original Hebrew foliation. Initial words and chapter titles in larger square characters. Page by page catchwords. Marginal additions and notes.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental cursive script of the 18th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'Notes on the Psalms. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Or. 4863.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: J.L. Hirschensohn: purchased from him by the British Museum on 11 February 1895: inscribed, flyleaf [ii]v.
